rse  to prepare young people for lives of service  leadership  and character  VMI cadets learn   through a rigorous military system  a demanding academic curriculum  and a robust athletic program  They leave VMI prepared to lead lives of strength  honor  and integrity   to serve their country and their communities as citizen soldiers  in times of peace and in times of deepest peril  THE CAMPAIGN FOR VMI Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7287 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org Belief in the Mission  skip to content VMI Virginia Military Institute Website Shopping Cart Menu Home Why VMI Matters Priorities How you can help  Strengthen Academics Prepare Leaders Support the Team Provide Opportunity Believe in the Mission Preserve Our Legacy Get Involved About Giving Videos Stories Progress Give Close Menu Home Why VMI Matters Priorities Get Involved About Giving Videos Stories Progress Give Traits Traits of a Cadet Preparing young people for lives of service  leadership  and character  SteadfastVMI cadets are faithful to the vision and mission of VMI  committed to reaching for something beyond themselves and dedicated to serving their country and their communities  They stand devoted to an uncommon purpose and a brilliant mission  CourageousVMI cadets choose to stand strong through four years of the adversative VMI system to achieve lofty goals in life  The step forward to grasp a greater understanding of who they are and what they stand for  They take hard strides to reach something of value  DedicatedVMI cadets enter a rigorous academic program where they cannot hide from their professors  They devote themselves to academic pursuits in the face of many other demands  and they succeed  HonorableVMI cadets commit themselves to the narrow walk of a single sanction honor code in which iron sharpens iron  They embrace the opportunity to hone their integrity  discipline  and civility in a world often lacking these basi